<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-06-06T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-06-06T17:00:00-05:00" n="658" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d658">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">812.52/2802: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Guaymas</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Yepis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Guaymas</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-06-06T16:00:00-06:00">June 6, 1938—4
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 10:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Referring to my telegram of June 3, 5 p.m., I have been informed that the
                            definite dotation of lands in the Yaqui that were to be made yesterday
                            were postponed without giving reason for it.</p>
                        <p>Embassy informed.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Yepis</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>